<html xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
       xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
       i18n:domain="plone">
<body>

<tal:comment tal:replace="nothing">
For use with ErikRose's CustomNav product, in the facilities section
In Plone 3, could in theory add 2 navigation portlets, each with a different root
But we want to style these 2 portlets differently and this is a quick and easy way of assigning portlet-specific ids
</tal:comment>

<div metal:define-macro="portlet"
       i18n:domain="plone"
       tal:omit-tag="">

	<dl class="portlet" id="typeOnePortlet"
		tal:define="basePath string:/facilities/find-a-facility">
		<dt class="portletHeader">
			<span class="portletTopLeft"></span>
			<a href="#"
			   class="tile"
			   tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}${basePath}">Find a facility that deals with&hellip;</a>
			<span class="portletTopRight"></span>
		</dt>
	
		<dd class="portletItem lastItem">
			<ul class="portletNavigationTree navTreeLevel0">
				<li tal:define="tree python:context.customNavtree(basePath=basePath)"
					tal:replace="structure python:context.portlet_navtree_macro(children=tree.get('children', []), show_children=True, isNaviTree=True)">
					Nav tree is inserted here.
				</li>
			</ul>
			<span class="portletBottomLeft"></span>
			<span class="portletBottomRight"></span>
		</dd>
	</dl>
	<br />
	<dl class="portlet" id="typeTwoPortlet"
		tal:define="basePath string:/facilities/find-by-location">
		<dt class="portletHeader">
			<span class="portletTopLeft"></span>
			<a href="#"
			   class="tile"
			   tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}${basePath}">Find a facility by location</a>
			<span class="portletTopRight"></span>
		</dt>
	
		<dd class="portletItem lastItem">
			<ul class="portletNavigationTree navTreeLevel0">
				<li tal:define="tree python:context.customNavtree(basePath=basePath)"
					tal:replace="structure python:context.portlet_navtree_macro(children=tree.get('children', []), show_children=True, isNaviTree=True)">
					Nav tree is inserted here.
				</li>
			</ul>
			<span class="portletBottomLeft"></span>
			<span class="portletBottomRight"></span>
		</dd>
	</dl>
</div>
</body>
</html>
